%N A397583 Number of ways to tile a 2 X n strip with one corner missing, using squares, dominoes, and T-shaped tetrominoes.
%C A397583 Compare to A397582 which counts these tilings for the full 2 X n strip (without a missing corner).
%H A397583 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,2,-1,-1).
%F A397583 G.f.: x/(1 - 3*x - 2*x^2 + x^3 + x^4).
%F A397583 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 2*a(n-2) - a(n-3) - a(n-4).
%F A397583 a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) + A397582(n-1).
%e A397583 Here is one of the a(6)=458 ways to tile this 2 X 6 strip (with one missing corner) using squares, dominoes, and T-shaped tetrominoes:
%e A397583    _________
%e A397583   |_   _| |_|_
%e A397583   |_|_|_|_|___|.
%t A397583 LinearRecurrence[{3, 2, -1, -1}, {0, 1, 3, 11}, 50]
